<i>Some people take
the winters here very well</i>

33:59.269 --> 34:00.602
<i>and there's others
that come down</i>

34:00.604 --> 34:02.337
<i>that just don't do well
with winter.</i>

34:02.339 --> 34:04.806
<i>You know there's not enough
going on for them.</i>

34:04.808 --> 34:06.508
<i>There's not enough
social life for them.</i>

34:06.510 --> 34:10.213
It's actually, I think
a pretty definite line

34:10.215 --> 34:12.315
between winter people
and non-winter people.

34:12.317 --> 34:14.283
<i>I mean, it's usually
fairly obvious.</i>

34:24.928 --> 34:26.996
<i>One of my main jobs
during the winter</i>

34:26.998 --> 34:31.400
<i>is to maintain communications
with the outside world</i>

34:31.402 --> 34:34.303
<i>This means regular trips
out across the ice shelf</i>

34:34.304 --> 34:37.406
<i>to the satellite station
on Black Island.</i>

