<i>because of the wind gauges
getting blown away.</i>

37:13.832 --> 37:17.568
Current wind speed
is 114 miles per hour

37:17.570 --> 37:19.137
or 99 knots...

37:19.139 --> 37:21.873
Make that 123 miles an hour.

37:23.442 --> 37:25.410
Although the camera
is on the tripod,

37:25.412 --> 37:27.845
you can see the picture
is actually quite shaky.

37:27.847 --> 37:29.046
That's because
the whole building

37:29.048 --> 37:31.048
is being shaken
by the 100-knot winds

37:31.050 --> 37:33.017
we've got at the moment.

37:33.019 --> 37:36.621
Just go for a walk out into
the main satellite dome here

37:36.623 --> 37:38.756
and show you what it looks like.

37:48.867 --> 37:51.469
As you can see,
it's a wee bit windy.

38:22.468 --> 38:23.734
I'll just show you
what it's like

38:23.736 --> 38:26.537
in the bunkhouse here
after the last storm.

38:44.656 --> 38:47.492
All the snow you can see
in the corner of the room here

38:47.494 --> 38:49.060
basically worked its way in

38:49.062 --> 38:51.629
through the tiny gaps
in the window seals.

38:52.764 --> 38:55.933
The wind speeds got up
to 222 miles an hour

38:55.935 --> 38:59.103
so this filled up in just
a matter of a few hours.

38:59.105 --> 39:01.639
And there's
a complete lounge suite

39:01.641 --> 39:02.707
in the corner over there.

39:02.709 --> 39:04.208
This is the fireplace

39:04.210 --> 39:08.280
that's normally used for
keeping the room warm.

40:13.947 --> 40:15.213
<i>In the middle of March,</i>

40:15.215 --> 40:18.016
<i>there's that magical
brief couple of weeks</i>

40:18.018 --> 40:20.018
<i>when the sun is rising
and setting</i>

40:20.020 --> 40:21.620
<i>like normal days</i>

40:21.622 --> 40:23.655
<i>and you can actually
leave the curtains open</i>

40:23.657 --> 40:25.057
<i>on your window at night</i>

40:25.059 --> 40:28.794
<i>to be woken up
by the sunrise in the morning.</i>

41:30.257 --> 41:34.028
<i>We were out
and the wind came up</i>

41:34.030 --> 41:37.064
and there was just moments
that it was so cold

41:37.066 --> 41:39.066
I could really

41:39.068 --> 41:41.402
actually feel the danger in it

41:41.404 --> 41:46.040
and feel the...
this crazy like mind thing

41:46.042 --> 41:48.042
that happened that was like...

41:48.044 --> 41:50.010
it was hard to focus
on anything

41:50.012 --> 41:54.048
except just getting out
of the conditions we were in

41:54.050 --> 41:56.817
and trying
to just be warm again.

41:57.986 --> 42:00.888
<i>It was really hard
to still focus on</i>

42:00.890 --> 42:03.390
<i>gathering all of the gear
and trying</i>

42:03.392 --> 42:05.259
<i>to do what needed to be done</i>

42:05.261 --> 42:07.261
<i>rather that just run</i>

42:07.263 --> 42:08.796
<i>for whatever vehicle</i>

42:08.798 --> 42:10.097
<i>or, you know, it was...</i>

42:10.099 --> 42:11.932
it was amazing how

42:11.934 --> 42:13.901
your instinct...
it just...

42:13.903 --> 42:15.102
it just snaps.

42:17.906 --> 42:21.375
<i>The first time where
I was just ridiculously cold</i>

42:21.377 --> 42:23.844
<i>was actually with you
just a few days ago</i>

42:23.846 --> 42:26.046
<i>taking the shift photo
up on the hill.</i>

42:26.048 --> 42:27.081
<i>Oh yeah.</i>

42:28.416 --> 42:29.483
<i>The wind was whipping
through there.</i>

42:29.485 --> 42:32.419
<i>I'd probably say it was
negative 80 with wind chill.</i>

42:32.421 --> 42:35.289
<i>And I remember
looking over at Chris Cavanaugh</i>

42:35.291 --> 42:37.791
<i>and tears were streaming
down his face.</i>

42:37.793 --> 42:39.793
<i>He didn't even know it
because it was so cold</i>

42:39.795 --> 42:41.729
<i>and the thing that surprised me</i>

42:41.731 --> 42:43.797
<i>is when he looked
at me a second time</i>

42:43.799 --> 42:46.200
those tears had frozen
to his face.

42:47.335 --> 42:50.037
<i>So that's...</i>

42:50.039 --> 42:51.939
<i>that made an impression on me.</i>

42:51.941 --> 42:53.907
<i>Maybe it's time to get inside.</i>

43:03.284 --> 43:05.119
We're about 30 K's away

43:05.121 --> 43:08.455
from the nearest seawater here
and it's still quite common

43:08.457 --> 43:10.090
to find guys like this.

43:10.092 --> 43:12.092
It's a mummified seal

43:12.094 --> 43:13.227
that's lost its way

43:13.229 --> 43:14.828
and wandered inland.

43:14.830 --> 43:16.897
It's an amazingly
common occurrence.

43:37.285 --> 43:39.153
<i>It's heartbreaking when you see</i>

43:39.155 --> 43:41.388
<i>animals in distress like this</i>

43:41.390 --> 43:43.157
<i>because we're not allowed
to interfere</i>

43:46.561 --> 43:49.129
<i>We just have to let nature
take its course.</i>

44:02.178 --> 44:04.012
<i>It can be really hard</i>

44:04.014 --> 44:07.048
<i>just being away from home
and hearing stories.</i>

44:07.050 --> 44:10.151
My sister just had a baby boy
a week ago.

44:10.153 --> 44:11.553
And that day was...

44:12.855 --> 44:13.888
really bittersweet.

44:13.890 --> 44:15.056
It was really cool,

44:15.058 --> 44:16.524
but man I wanted nothing
more than

44:16.526 --> 44:17.926
to get the hell out of here

44:17.928 --> 44:18.960
just for a day.

44:18.962 --> 44:20.962
Go home and enjoy that moment

44:20.964 --> 44:23.298
with my family
because they were all together

44:23.300 --> 44:25.433
and then I was down here,

44:25.435 --> 44:28.036
you know,
shooting emails out all day

44:28.038 --> 44:29.370
and then on the phone
a couple times

44:29.372 --> 44:30.505
and that was really really hard.

44:32.241 --> 44:33.942
So for me,

44:33.944 --> 44:36.611
what sucks is definitely

44:36.613 --> 44:38.847
missing family,
but more importantly

44:38.849 --> 44:40.849
missing these big moments
with them,

44:40.851 --> 44:41.850
you know,

44:41.852 --> 44:43.484
my family's lives back home.

44:47.556 --> 44:49.524
<i>Well, I mean,
first of all,</i>

44:49.526 --> 44:51.125
<i>I had my concerns.</i>

44:51.127 --> 44:52.527
<i>And this is what I do
always in my life</i>

44:52.529 --> 44:53.561
<i>that if I'm ever feeling low</i>

44:53.563 --> 44:55.597
<i>I have things around
just in case.</i>

44:55.599 --> 44:58.099
<i>One of the things is I brought
a lot of photos of my family</i>

44:58.101 --> 45:00.101
<i>so I have them taped
to my fridge.</i>

45:00.103 --> 45:01.402
And then I just know

45:01.404 --> 45:02.637
that there's always
people on my side

45:02.639 --> 45:05.406
even if it seems like the walls
are closing in down here.

45:15.384 --> 45:17.585
<i>It was just
like any other day</i>

45:17.587 --> 45:18.453
<i>and the phone rang.</i>

45:20.522 --> 45:22.156
<i>It was my grandmother</i>

45:22.158 --> 45:24.359
<i>and immediately
my heart sunk because</i>

45:24.361 --> 45:26.127
<i>I knew something was wrong.</i>

45:28.364 --> 45:31.566
<i>And she told me that
my father had passed away</i>

45:31.568 --> 45:33.167
<i>and...</i>

45:34.169 --> 45:35.370
<i>it was quite a shock.</i>

45:36.405 --> 45:38.206
<i>I never expected that</i>

45:38.208 --> 45:41.976
<i>it was...
it was really difficult.</i>

45:41.978 --> 45:44.679
<i>I mean,
when you lose a parent</i>

45:44.681 --> 45:48.549
<i>it's a big thing.
And to not be able</i>

45:48.551 --> 45:51.152
<i>to be with your family
during that time</i>

45:51.154 --> 45:54.656
<i>and not being able
to go to the funeral.</i>

45:54.658 --> 45:58.526
<i>I just...
it leaves things unfinished.</i>

46:04.266 --> 46:07.268
<i>I wanted to be there
for my family.</i>

46:07.270 --> 46:08.970
<i>I needed to be there</i>

46:08.972 --> 46:09.971
<i>and I couldn't.</i>

46:26.555 --> 46:29.225
<i>It's probably the most
isolated place on the planet</i>

46:29.227 --> 46:31.494
and that's really hard
to adjust to.

46:31.496 --> 46:33.730
I can see people who...

46:33.732 --> 46:36.433
one winter would be
enough for them.

46:39.303 --> 46:41.071
<i>It's really hard for a lot
of people.</i>

46:54.151 --> 46:55.452
<i>I found that there
was this curve</i>

46:55.454 --> 46:57.320
<i>where I just really
started missing like</i>

46:57.322 --> 46:58.722
<i>eating sushi and Indian food</i>

46:58.724 --> 47:00.190
<i>and going to movies
and just like...</i>

47:00.192 --> 47:01.257
the life.

47:01.259 --> 47:02.492
And then it became like so much

47:02.494 --> 47:04.160
that I just really
missed it a lot

47:04.162 --> 47:07.130
and then it just
dropped off and...

47:07.132 --> 47:08.231
I don't miss...

47:08.233 --> 47:09.632
I don't know if it's like

47:09.634 --> 47:11.368
a post-traumatic stress
disorder response

47:11.370 --> 47:12.736
or I don't want to think
about what I miss

47:12.738 --> 47:14.204
or I'll get really distressed
or what it is,

47:14.206 --> 47:16.573
but there's
not a lot that I miss.

47:16.575 --> 47:19.142
I've been thinking
about avocados lately.

47:19.144 --> 47:21.077
An avocado would be nice.

47:21.079 --> 47:22.312
You may want to have

47:23.381 --> 47:25.181
a toast with avocado

47:25.183 --> 47:27.717
and then you can only
dream about it.

47:27.719 --> 47:29.285
But simple as...

47:31.288 --> 47:33.757
black tea with fresh milk

47:33.759 --> 47:35.325
or perhaps even better

47:35.327 --> 47:37.093
with fresh cream.

47:37.095 --> 47:38.194
<i>Dark bread.</i>

47:39.697 --> 47:40.663
<i>Cauliflower.</i>

47:41.532 --> 47:43.199
<i>It's brilliant.</i>

47:43.201 --> 47:46.169
<i>Just to have
a fresh head of cauliflower</i>

47:46.171 --> 47:47.337
<i>would be very nice now.</i>

47:53.110 --> 47:54.477
Noooooo!

47:56.114 --> 47:58.415
It's no good we can't do
anything for him now

47:58.417 --> 48:00.283
<i>In the winter of 2008,</i>

48:00.285 --> 48:01.785
<i>I started a 48-hour</i>

48:01.787 --> 48:03.386
<i>Antarctic film festival.</i>

48:07.525 --> 48:11.294
<i>and invited all the bases
on the continent to participate.</i>

48:16.267 --> 48:17.634
<i>One of the greatest pleasures</i>

48:17.636 --> 48:19.502
<i>of watching these films
each year</i>

48:19.504 --> 48:23.173
<i>is just getting to see what
the other bases look like...</i>

48:26.477 --> 48:27.744
<i>and who else is out there</i>

48:27.746 --> 48:29.646
<i>wintering over
on the ice.</i>

48:46.330 --> 48:47.697
<i>Carolina,</i>

48:47.699 --> 48:48.798
<i>great to hear your voice.</i>

48:48.800 --> 48:50.300
Yes how are you?

48:51.602 --> 48:53.636
I'm good. Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

48:53.638 --> 48:54.804
Everything's good here.

48:54.806 --> 48:56.474
Just um...

48:56.476 --> 48:57.274
having...

48:57.276 --> 48:59.510
having my breakfast
and some coffee.

49:02.280 --> 49:04.248
<i>How are your parents?</i>

49:26.671 --> 49:28.539
<i>Another hour?
- Ummm.</i>

49:32.878 --> 49:34.912
<i>Are we ever going
to see the sun again?</i>

49:35.747 --> 49:36.881
One day.

50:04.743 --> 50:06.410
<i>Guess you start to get used</i>

50:06.412 --> 50:08.179
<i>to living in a world
without light.</i>

50:11.416 --> 50:14.285
<i>The days get short
and the nights get long</i>

50:14.287 --> 50:16.420
<i>'till the nights get real long.</i>

50:16.422 --> 50:18.255
<i>Towards the end
of the month there...</i>

50:19.257 --> 50:20.624
there's no more sun

50:20.626 --> 50:23.894
and...
that's all she wrote.

50:49.888 --> 50:51.922
<i>I was scared
of the coming darkness</i>

50:51.924 --> 50:53.290
<i>the coming darkness</i>

50:53.292 --> 50:56.327
<i>for so many months
and I thought</i>

50:56.329 --> 50:57.561
is that going to get to me?

50:57.563 --> 50:59.230
Is that going to make me...

50:59.232 --> 51:00.331
well, how will that affect me?

51:00.333 --> 51:02.700
I was pretty scared of that
and how that might...

51:02.702 --> 51:05.369
<i>just change me.</i>

51:07.272 --> 51:08.839
<i>I would correspond
with winter-overs</i>

51:08.841 --> 51:10.441
<i>when I was off the ice</i>

51:10.443 --> 51:11.775
<i>and you could just
see it in their emails.</i>

51:12.844 --> 51:13.711
They would change.

51:13.713 --> 51:16.280
And I'm like wow
is that going to change me?

51:16.282 --> 51:17.348
I don't know.

51:22.788 --> 51:25.457
<i>As it is the light changes
enough in the sky</i>

51:25.459 --> 51:26.825
<i>that it's still seems to me</i>

51:26.827 --> 51:29.427
<i>that the sun is just
around the corner.</i>

51:29.429 --> 51:31.896
<i>And I think that's had a great
effect on me because</i>

51:31.898 --> 51:32.764
<i>it just reminds me that no,</i>

51:32.766 --> 51:33.999
<i>it's not just dark.</i>

51:34.900 --> 51:35.767
<i>Attention all stations</i>

51:35.769 --> 51:38.570
<i>standby for a severe
weather condition announcement.</i>

51:38.572 --> 51:41.406
<i>McMurdo weather has set
Severe Weather Condition One</i>

51:43.910 --> 51:46.945
<i>McMurdo Station, T-site,
Arrival Heights,</i>

51:46.947 --> 51:48.480
<i>Pegasus Field,</i>

51:48.482 --> 51:50.283
<i>Williams Field,
road to Williams Field...</i>

51:51.718 --> 51:52.918
Check this out.

51:55.722 --> 51:59.825
This is the entryway
to our dorm.

51:59.827 --> 52:02.361
Normally this has carpet
on the ground

52:02.363 --> 52:04.630
and the walls are just
normally walls, you know,

52:04.632 --> 52:05.898
But...

52:05.900 --> 52:07.500
We're going to open
the door right now

52:07.502 --> 52:08.668
and it's a little bit
like opening up

52:08.670 --> 52:09.835
the door to another world.

52:11.438 --> 52:13.005
Are you ready?

52:23.050 --> 52:25.017
It's a little bit blowy
out there right now.

52:43.704 --> 52:45.971
<i>You know,
when you watch television here</i>

52:45.973 --> 52:47.106
<i>and you see all the things</i>

52:47.108 --> 52:48.941
<i>that are going wrong
in the world</i>

52:48.943 --> 52:50.376
<i>you know that's...</i>

52:50.378 --> 52:51.544
<i>it's like thank
goodness I'm here.</i>

52:51.546 --> 52:53.846
<i>But then you also
then watch shows where</i>

52:53.848 --> 52:56.549
<i>you see swaying palm trees</i>

52:57.684 --> 52:59.819
<i>and people laughing</i>

52:59.821 --> 53:01.554
and bucolic scenes

53:01.556 --> 53:02.555
and you're not there.

53:02.557 --> 53:04.590
You're here where it's
dark and cold and windy.

