01:13:44.743 --> 01:13:46.978
<i>It's kind of crazy.</i>

01:13:46.980 --> 01:13:49.747
<i>I think people either
are energized by it</i>

01:13:49.749 --> 01:13:51.048
<i>or just the opposite.</i>

01:13:51.050 --> 01:13:53.384
They have energy drawn
from them

01:13:53.386 --> 01:13:55.620
and I would tend to be
one of those people

01:13:55.622 --> 01:13:57.788
who have energy drawn from me.

01:13:57.790 --> 01:14:00.691
I'm not a big fan
of when all the folks come in.

01:14:04.930 --> 01:14:07.331
<i>For six months you've seen
only the same people every day.</i>

01:14:07.333 --> 01:14:09.200
<i>There hasn't been anyone new.</i>

01:14:09.202 --> 01:14:12.403
<i>All of a sudden you've got all
these new people coming through.</i>

01:14:12.405 --> 01:14:15.306
<i>Kind of this feeling
of glee and happiness</i>

01:14:15.308 --> 01:14:17.742
mixed with revulsion
like, "Aggghhh, stay away!"

01:14:22.814 --> 01:14:25.049
And I've even seen
winter-overs kind of hide

01:14:25.051 --> 01:14:27.752
behind corners
and kind of look out.

01:14:34.860 --> 01:14:37.094
<i>We've had a closed community
over the winter</i>

01:14:37.096 --> 01:14:39.163
<i>and there's been no germs,
no one gets sick.</i>

01:14:39.165 --> 01:14:42.767
<i>But new people come in...
new germs.</i>

01:14:42.769 --> 01:14:45.336
<i>They all have all this energy
and they're orange.</i>

01:14:45.338 --> 01:14:47.705
<i>I mean we always talk
about the orange people</i>

01:14:47.707 --> 01:14:48.773
<i>because they're tanned.</i>

01:14:49.941 --> 01:14:53.110
You don't really realize
how pale we all are

01:14:53.112 --> 01:14:54.845
from lack of sunshine.

01:15:01.119 --> 01:15:02.787
<i>Just walking through the galley,</i>

01:15:02.789 --> 01:15:05.322
I felt like I was moving
at this little pace

01:15:05.324 --> 01:15:07.692
and everyone else
was rushing around...

01:15:07.694 --> 01:15:09.093
around me.

01:15:16.001 --> 01:15:19.403
I was surprised at how
territorial we all were.

01:15:19.405 --> 01:15:22.740
I remember getting back
from the flight line

01:15:22.742 --> 01:15:24.141
and coming straight to dinner.

01:15:25.043 --> 01:15:28.112
And I got my tray
and my plate

01:15:28.947 --> 01:15:32.183
<i>and I looked up
and I saw a line.</i>

01:15:32.185 --> 01:15:34.385
<i>And I was so livid</i>

01:15:34.387 --> 01:15:36.353
<i>that I had to wait in line.</i>

01:15:37.456 --> 01:15:38.456
<i>These new people they</i>

01:15:38.458 --> 01:15:39.423
<i>weren't with the program yet.</i>

01:15:39.425 --> 01:15:41.125
<i>They didn't know
what they were doing</i>

01:15:41.127 --> 01:15:43.094
<i>the whole routine
was messed up.</i>

01:15:43.096 --> 01:15:44.061
<i>And I was so livid.</i>

01:15:44.063 --> 01:15:46.864
<i>I felt like I could have
stabbed somebody with a fork.</i>

01:15:50.736 --> 01:15:52.303
<i>And I didn't understand it.</i>

01:15:52.305 --> 01:15:54.271
<i>I'm like,
"Why am I so angry?"</i>

01:16:02.014 --> 01:16:03.148
I couldn't eat in the galley.

01:16:03.150 --> 01:16:04.816
I went up to my room.

01:16:04.818 --> 01:16:06.485
And...
I'm sitting in my room

01:16:06.487 --> 01:16:08.186
for about 5 minutes
contemplating about

01:16:08.188 --> 01:16:10.756
why I was so angry.

01:16:10.758 --> 01:16:12.924
And then I get knocks on my door

01:16:12.926 --> 01:16:15.293
and it's the rest
of the Firehouse.

01:16:15.295 --> 01:16:16.828
"Can we eat in here with you?"

01:16:17.363 --> 01:16:18.797
Yeah.

01:16:18.799 --> 01:16:19.965
So we sat down
and for half an hour

01:16:19.967 --> 01:16:21.366
we ate our meals watching TV.

01:16:22.401 --> 01:16:25.170
Didn't say a word to each other
and it was beautiful.

01:16:45.458 --> 01:16:46.525
<i>The first few days,</i>

01:16:46.527 --> 01:16:48.026
<i>or maybe the first week,</i>

01:16:48.028 --> 01:16:50.162
<i>is kind of a culture shock.</i>

01:16:51.297 --> 01:16:53.198
You know,
the dynamics change.

01:16:53.200 --> 01:16:54.833
The noise level rises.

01:16:55.868 --> 01:16:59.070
<i>But after that
the new people that come here</i>

01:16:59.072 --> 01:17:01.206
<i>they have so much energy</i>

01:17:01.208 --> 01:17:03.909
<i>and I find that it brings me up.</i>

01:17:04.010 --> 01:17:06.945
<i>And I actually get more excited
about getting stuff done</i>

01:17:06.947 --> 01:17:08.847
<i>and moving around.</i>

01:17:08.849 --> 01:17:09.915
It kind of wakes me up.

01:17:12.051 --> 01:17:14.486
Keri, how does it feel to have
a fresh apple after 6 months?

01:17:19.458 --> 01:17:20.959
Orange, apple?

01:17:20.961 --> 01:17:22.127
Why don't you take
that behind doors?

01:17:22.129 --> 01:17:23.862
<i>I'm sure I'll get one very soon.</i>

01:17:28.534 --> 01:17:30.569
Be gentle with the banana.

01:18:02.368 --> 01:18:03.869
<i>I would love to be able</i>

01:18:03.871 --> 01:18:05.337
<i>to show the people
who I love the most</i>

01:18:05.339 --> 01:18:06.638
<i>what it looks like down here...</i>

01:18:06.640 --> 01:18:08.340
what the sky looks like
down here in winter.

01:18:12.645 --> 01:18:14.379
<i>Because they're never
going to see it.</i>

01:18:24.624 --> 01:18:26.091
<i>It's funny.</i>

01:18:26.093 --> 01:18:28.227
<i>Right before winter started
we'd tell these stories</i>

01:18:28.229 --> 01:18:32.265
<i>about how you'd get T3
and you get pale</i>

01:18:32.267 --> 01:18:35.501
<i>and you're just
emotional sometimes.</i>

01:18:35.503 --> 01:18:37.638
<i>And these people
who have never wintered</i>

01:18:37.640 --> 01:18:39.106
<i>are looking at us
like we're freaks.</i>

01:18:39.108 --> 01:18:40.440
<i>Like why would you ever</i>

01:18:40.442 --> 01:18:42.576
<i>put yourself through
something like that?</i>

01:18:48.583 --> 01:18:50.350
<i>And then, at the end,</i>

01:18:52.120 --> 01:18:53.287
<i>we'd look at each other and say,</i>

01:18:54.455 --> 01:18:55.589
"Winter's the best.

01:18:57.592 --> 01:18:58.692
It's the greatest. "

01:19:09.137 --> 01:19:11.238
<i>I try and explain
the experience,</i>

01:19:11.240 --> 01:19:14.308
<i>the Antarctic experience,
to people back home,</i>

01:19:14.310 --> 01:19:16.610
<i>and they love
hearing about it.</i>

01:19:16.612 --> 01:19:18.412
<i>The stories and what it's like.</i>

01:19:19.347 --> 01:19:22.482
<i>But, you know that...</i>

01:19:22.484 --> 01:19:24.418
they just...
they will never get it.

01:19:24.420 --> 01:19:29.222
They'll never fully comprehend
what it's like down here.

01:20:46.734 --> 01:20:49.302
So if you were to spend
another year down here

01:20:49.304 --> 01:20:51.171
<i>what would you do differently?</i>

01:20:52.473 --> 01:20:54.709
<i>Not bring as much stuff.</i>

01:21:08.123 --> 01:21:10.558
I've met some of the best people
in the world here.

01:21:10.560 --> 01:21:14.395
And I think a lot of that is
because of the fact

01:21:14.397 --> 01:21:16.097
that those of us that come here

01:21:16.099 --> 01:21:18.433
<i>always have a kind
of a spirit of adventure.</i>

01:21:18.435 --> 01:21:22.470
<i>And that's something
that kind of binds us together.</i>

01:21:33.682 --> 01:21:35.450
<i>These might be...</i>

01:21:35.452 --> 01:21:37.418
<i>the golden years of Antarctica.</i>

01:21:41.824 --> 01:21:44.392
<i>Right now,
what is being done is science.</i>

01:21:44.394 --> 01:21:46.094
<i>Right now there's
a treaty that says</i>

01:21:46.096 --> 01:21:48.629
<i>you get to be here
to cooperate,</i>

01:21:48.631 --> 01:21:49.464
<i>look for peace,</i>

01:21:49.466 --> 01:21:51.532
<i>and look for knowledge
for mankind.</i>

01:21:51.534 --> 01:21:54.168
<i>And I just can't think
of another place</i>

01:21:54.170 --> 01:21:56.771
<i>where that's really going on
so I feel really privileged</i>

01:21:56.773 --> 01:21:59.774
to be a citizen
of Antarctica right now.

01:21:59.776 --> 01:22:01.442
I really really do.

01:22:01.444 --> 01:22:04.145
<i>And some day,
somebody is going to find a way</i>

01:22:04.147 --> 01:22:05.146
<i>to get oil commercially.</i>

01:22:05.148 --> 01:22:06.881
<i>And some day,
the treaty is going to end</i>

01:22:06.883 --> 01:22:10.251
<i>And some day,
you know...</i>

01:22:10.253 --> 01:22:12.320
<i>I don't know that we'll always
be able to play as nice</i>

01:22:12.322 --> 01:22:14.355
<i>as we can right now.</i>

01:22:40.349 --> 01:22:43.451
<i>You come down here
out of a sense of adventure.</i>

01:22:45.621 --> 01:22:47.688
<i>But then it gets
its hooks in you.</i>

01:22:47.690 --> 01:22:49.423
<i>and you realize</i>

01:22:49.425 --> 01:22:51.359
<i>how magic and fragile
it all is.</i>

01:22:51.361 --> 01:22:53.694
<i>And if we're not careful,</i>

01:22:53.696 --> 01:22:55.630
<i>if we're not conscientious,</i>

01:22:55.632 --> 01:22:57.598
<i>It could all get ruined.</i>

01:23:16.185 --> 01:23:19.253
<i>Imagine you live in a house.</i>

01:23:19.255 --> 01:23:22.591
<i>And this is just one room
in your house...</i>

01:23:22.593 --> 01:23:24.960
<i>a cold room
where nobody lives.</i>

01:23:24.962 --> 01:23:27.829
<i>But it's still
a room in your house</i>

01:23:27.831 --> 01:23:31.633
<i>and as such you have
to care about this room.</i>

01:23:31.635 --> 01:23:34.970
<i>And you have to know
about what's going on there.</i>

01:23:47.817 --> 01:23:50.953
<i>There is a good expression
in the English language:</i>

01:23:50.955 --> 01:23:52.421
<i>peace of mind.</i>

01:23:52.423 --> 01:23:53.956
I really like it.

01:23:53.958 --> 01:23:58.228
Peace of mind
is a very nice thing to have.

01:24:07.938 --> 01:24:10.406
<i>The friends you make
and the memories</i>

01:24:10.408 --> 01:24:13.343
<i>that you take from here
last a lifetime.</i>

01:24:13.345 --> 01:24:15.912
<i>I've met guys who were
down here 50 years ago</i>

01:24:15.914 --> 01:24:17.480
who would like nothing
more in the world

01:24:17.482 --> 01:24:19.682
than the chance
to come back again...

01:24:19.684 --> 01:24:21.284
<i>just one more time.</i>

01:24:26.624 --> 01:24:29.993
<i>You know you can never really
call this place home.</i>

01:24:29.995 --> 01:24:33.463
<i>But at the same time
there's a familiarity</i>

01:24:33.465 --> 01:24:35.465
<i>that just builds up.</i>

01:24:38.502 --> 01:24:40.970
<i>I definitely long for it
when I'm away.</i>

01:25:28.085 --> 01:25:30.420
<i>I fully expect
that my time here</i>

01:25:30.422 --> 01:25:32.588
<i>is not going to end
on my terms.</i>

01:25:33.857 --> 01:25:35.692
<i>The program could change</i>

01:25:35.694 --> 01:25:37.393
<i>or I might not pass
the physical...</i>

01:25:38.562 --> 01:25:40.396
<i>or there might not be a job.</i>

01:25:43.767 --> 01:25:46.469
<i>No one gets to stay
here indefinitely.</i>

01:25:52.610 --> 01:25:56.013
<i>And then the time comes
when it's you turn to leave</i>

01:25:56.015 --> 01:25:58.349
<i>and you never really
do know for sure</i>

01:25:58.351 --> 01:26:00.017
<i>if you'll ever be back again.</i>

01:27:11.790 --> 01:27:14.992
<i>One of the things I recall</i>

01:27:14.994 --> 01:27:18.095
<i>in the process
of reacclimating to society</i>

01:27:18.097 --> 01:27:21.098
<i>was a Monday morning.</i>

01:27:21.100 --> 01:27:24.468
<i>It's probably 8:30
in the morning</i>

01:27:24.470 --> 01:27:26.904
<i>and I am stuck in traffic.</i>

01:27:28.206 --> 01:27:30.641
<i>I remember looking
at all the cars around me.</i>

01:27:30.643 --> 01:27:33.744
<i>Everybody's...
they're in their own little...</i>

01:27:33.746 --> 01:27:36.480
<i>They're in the grind
of the world.</i>

01:27:36.482 --> 01:27:39.883
<i>And I can't help
but look at everybody else</i>

01:27:39.885 --> 01:27:41.785
<i>and think...</i>

01:27:41.787 --> 01:27:42.786
<i>they're cattle.</i>

01:27:42.788 --> 01:27:46.590
<i>It's just one big herd
moving from point A to point B.</i>

01:27:46.592 --> 01:27:50.794
<i>and... at that point</i>

01:27:50.796 --> 01:27:52.863
<i>I wanted to be back
on the Ice again.</i>

01:28:33.005 --> 01:28:34.539
<i>It's not until you get
off the Ice</i>

01:28:34.541 --> 01:28:37.742
<i>that you realize the absence
of smell that we have here...</i>

01:28:37.744 --> 01:28:39.677
<i>the absence of odors.</i>

01:28:39.679 --> 01:28:42.180
<i>So yeah...</i>

01:28:42.182 --> 01:28:44.115
<i>you can go
to the Botanical Gardens</i>

01:28:44.117 --> 01:28:46.084
<i>for an olfactory overload.</i>

01:28:57.997 --> 01:29:01.032
<i>I'm going to go
to the New World Supermarket</i>

01:29:01.034 --> 01:29:03.601
<i>and I'm going to stand
in the produce section</i>

01:29:03.603 --> 01:29:05.603
<i>and just smell the air</i>

01:29:05.605 --> 01:29:06.905
<i>for about 15 minutes.</i>

01:29:06.907 --> 01:29:11.843
some really good
chewy crusty bread,

01:29:11.845 --> 01:29:14.145
a hunk of really good
blue cheese,

01:29:14.147 --> 01:29:17.849
an avocado and some
red grapes with no seeds.

01:29:17.851 --> 01:29:22.821
And that's what I'm going to eat
for like 3 meals.

01:29:22.823 --> 01:29:25.858
There comes a point
in the winter

01:29:25.860 --> 01:29:28.027
when...

01:29:28.029 --> 01:29:29.728
at least us, the guys,

01:29:29.730 --> 01:29:30.796
us in the Firehouse,

01:29:30.798 --> 01:29:32.665
we stop talking about women.

01:29:32.667 --> 01:29:35.601
And we start talking
about food

01:29:35.603 --> 01:29:38.070
because it's a much more
realistic prospect.

01:29:40.006 --> 01:29:41.674
So...

01:29:41.676 --> 01:29:43.642
I've narrowed it down.
I'm going to go

01:29:43.644 --> 01:29:46.312
and I'm going to have
steak and lobster.

01:29:47.614 --> 01:29:49.214
I'm going to splurge.

01:29:50.183 --> 01:29:53.085
Fresh vegetables with flavor.

01:29:53.087 --> 01:29:57.823
A bean burrito from Taco Bell.

01:29:57.825 --> 01:29:58.891
<i>Dark bread.</i>

01:30:00.026 --> 01:30:01.093
Avocado.

01:30:03.330 --> 01:30:04.630
Cauliflower.

01:30:04.632 --> 01:30:06.999
A bowl of cornflakes
with real milk

01:30:07.001 --> 01:30:09.101
and sliced bananas.

01:30:09.103 --> 01:30:12.338
Eggs Benedict at the Boulevard
in New Zealand.

01:30:12.340 --> 01:30:15.908
Anything in Christchurch
is always good.

01:30:16.009 --> 01:30:17.376
Anything non-institutional.

01:30:19.212 --> 01:30:22.815
When I get back to New Zealand
the first thing I long to do

01:30:22.817 --> 01:30:25.751
well first, first thing is go
through the Botanic Gardens

01:30:25.753 --> 01:30:28.921
and just touch the grass
and smell the flowers.

01:30:28.923 --> 01:30:31.056
But then I try to get
to the ocean

01:30:31.058 --> 01:30:32.091
to see that motion I guess.

01:30:32.093 --> 01:30:34.230
<i>- You're standing on
the ocean now. - Exactly.</i>

01:30:34.295 --> 01:30:36.729
That's what's so funny.
And I'm a mountain girl,

01:30:36.731 --> 01:30:38.330
so it's never been
a draw before.

01:30:42.135 --> 01:30:44.169
<i>Walk barefoot in grass.</i>

01:30:48.242 --> 01:30:51.011
<i>I'm going to fly straight home
to Washington State.</i>

01:30:51.013 --> 01:30:54.714
And I'm going to fly-fish
my brains out for about 3 weeks

01:30:54.716 --> 01:30:56.249
going for salmon and steel head.

01:30:56.251 --> 01:30:59.119
And when I puke,
I think that's when I'll stop.

01:31:00.388 --> 01:31:02.889
I really like going to sleep
in my own bed.

01:31:02.891 --> 01:31:05.258
I really like...
Oh rain.

01:31:05.260 --> 01:31:07.193
Just hearing the rain
and seeing it

01:31:07.195 --> 01:31:09.696
feeling it again.
Wonderful

01:31:10.364 --> 01:31:12.666
<i>I plan on doing nothing.</i>

01:31:12.668 --> 01:31:15.168
I hope it rains at least one day
while I'm in Christchurch,

01:31:15.170 --> 01:31:17.037
just so I can
wander around in the rain.

01:31:17.039 --> 01:31:17.837
I'd love that.

01:31:17.839 --> 01:31:21.041
I hope it's...
I want some rain.

01:31:24.378 --> 01:31:26.780
Have a decent sleep.

01:31:27.715 --> 01:31:29.949
Have a decent sleep
for a few days.

01:31:31.085 --> 01:31:32.819
I don't know.

01:31:33.954 --> 01:31:36.322
Check into a hotel room
and take a bath.

01:31:49.904 --> 01:31:51.438
My brain is freezing.

01:31:52.907 --> 01:31:53.907
Let me think.

01:31:53.909 --> 01:31:56.743
I think my brain is freezing now
and I can't think.

01:31:59.113 --> 01:32:00.880
Skip that question.

